headline: Realty Income (O): Does New £900M Sterling Loan Change the Valuation Story?
summary: Realty Income (O) just closed a sizable £900 million unsecured term loan in Sterling, aiming to repay outstanding credit facility borrowings and get ahead of an upcoming loan maturity through proactive refinancing. The company also secured a fixed 4.3% interest rate with swaps, providing greater predictability for its financing costs. See our latest analysis for Realty Income.
